<% content_for(:title) do %>
    Choose a Posting App
<% end %>

<% content_for(:extracss) do %>
<style>
#box-table-a
{
  /**font-family: "Lucida Sans Unicode", "Lucida Grande", Sans-Serif;**/
  font-size: 12px;
  width: 350px;
  text-align: left;
  border-collapse: collapse;
}
#box-table-a th
{
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: normal;
  padding: 8px;
  background: #242424;
  border-top: 4px solid #ffffff;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #fff;
  color: #ffffff;
}
#box-table-a td
{
  padding: 8px;
  /**background: #e8edff; **/
  border-bottom: 1px solid #fff;
  /**color: #669;**/
  border-top: 1px solid transparent;
}
#box-table-a tr:hover td
{
  background: #f4f0ec;
  /**color: #339;**/
}

#box-table-a .box-table-a-yes
{
  /**background: #f4f0ec;**/
}

#box-table-a .box-table-a-no
{
  background: #F5A9A9;
}

#box-table-a .box-table-a-dev
{
  background: #1BE070;
}

#box-table-a .box-table-a-pos
{
  background: #E0DD1B;
}

</style>
<% end %>

<h2 class="page-header">Select a Privly Application</h2>

<div class="row-fluid">
  <div class="span6">
    <p>Each app gives you different capabilities. Choose whichever one is most appropriate for your communication needs. You can manage the data generated by each of these posting apps on your <%= link_to "post management page", posts_path %>. More applications will be added in time.</p>
  
    <ul>
      <li>
        <%= link_to 'ZeroBin', '/apps/ZeroBin/new.html' %> - <strong>Link Encryption</strong>: Your content is encrypted by text that is stored on the link. This content server will not be able to decrypt the content without considerable computational effort.
      </li>
      <li>
        <%= link_to 'PlainPost', "/apps/PlainPost/new.html" %> - <strong>Not Encrypted</strong>: This server will have full access to the content posted with this application.
      </li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Table Key</h3>
    <p>
      <ul>
        <li>Yes: This is implemented.</li>
        <li>No: This is not possible for this application.</li>
        <li>Possible: It can be done, but no one is working on it.</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    
  </div>
  
  <div class="span6">
    <table id="box-table-a" summary="Privacy Capabilities">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Privacy Capability</th>
          <th scope="col">ZeroBin</th>
          <th scope="col">Plain Post</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>This server can't read it</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-no">No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>"Good Bots" won't index public content when they have access to the host page</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>"Bad Bots" won't index public content when they have access to the host page</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-no">No</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-no">No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>"Bots" won't index private content when they have access to the host page</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  
    <table id="box-table-a" summary="Security Capabilities">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Security Capability</th>
          <th scope="col">ZeroBin</th>
          <th scope="col">Plain Post</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Link Required for Access</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Compromising the server does not compromise the content</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-no">No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Compromising the host page does not compromise public content</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-no">No</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-no">No</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Compromising the host page does not compromise private content</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Compromising the host page and this server does not compromise content</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-no">No</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-no">No</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    
    <table id="box-table-a" summary="Functionality Capabilities">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Functionality Capability</th>
          <th scope="col">ZeroBin</th>
          <th scope="col">Plain Post</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>You can read the content on this server without the original link</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-no">
            No
          </td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Accepts Markdown Format</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-pos">
            Possible
          </td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Accepts non-text Content</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-pos">Possible</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-pos">Possible</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Supports Public Content (no pre-provisioning keys)</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Edit Content after Creation</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Timed Destruction of Content</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
          <td class="box-table-a-yes">Yes</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>